htds

Class DataLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • htds.DataLog

  • public class DataLog
extends java.lang.Object
    The DataLog class is a data structure that stores logging information about Data objects read from a phone list (a file) A single DataLog object is created for every file read by the Uploader This DataLog object will be referenced by every Data object created in the upload activity through the DataLog id The DataLog class records the userID who uploaded the file, the file name, and the date of the activity Once a DataLog is created, it cannot be modified
    Author:
    Qutaiba
